27/10/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Authorities on Tuesday (26 October) blamed the separatist Kurdistan Workers Party (PKK), renamed KONGRA-GEL, for a bomb attack on the Batman oil pipeline in southeast Turkey earlier in the day. 
Officials say the attack -- the third in a week -- resulted in the leaking of approximately 200 barrels of crude oil. 
(NTV, Turks.us - 26/10/04)
